<br>
     I just thought I would take a minute to put this quest on the message board for all of those who may be interested.  Its fairly involved but if things go right it can be done in a few hours and the end result is pretty nice.<br>
<br>
(1)   Obtain a Sceptre of the Coldain Ancients found on Queen Drachnia in Crystal Caverns (she drops it everytime she spawns I believe)<br>
<br>
(2)   Go to Thurgadin and find Erdarf Restil.  He is in a bar down past the bank towards the temple.  I think it is the first building on the left past the bank.  Give Erdarf the Sceptre and he will give you back a gem (Gem of Persuasion) that looks like a lightstone.  <br>
<br>
(3)   Obtain a Blood Wolf Harness found on a Drakkel Blood Wolf in Great Divide.  These are somewhat of a rare spawn so you will need a tracker.   The harness can also be bought from players or from merhcant in which players have sold them to since this item is not no drop.<br>
<br>
(4)   Now you will need to find Vores the Hunter in Great Divide.  If you follow the stream from thurgadin through the Shardwum cave and out the other side you will see a small tent with a fire just off of the stream bed to the right.  This is where Vores should be.  Give him the Gem of Persuasion and the Blood Wolf Harness.  *note that a Crested Blood Wolf Harness will NOT work.   In return he gives you back a Harness of Control.<br>
<br>
(5)   Now you will want to make sure the the Shardwurm Broodmother is up in the cave and that Grakl Dwarfkiller and Fergul Frostsky are up in the fort.<br>
<br>
(6)   If all of the named NPC's are up as described above then find the Shardwurm Broodmother in the shardwurm caves and give her the Harness of Control.  She will then start to exit the cave.  Now you need to get back to the front of the fort ASAP and get ready.<br>
<br>
(7)   Once Broodmother has the harness, she leaves the cave and heads to the fort.  Fergul and Grakl will come out of the fort and eventually set up on the NW side of the fort.  DO NOT aggro Fergul or Grakl or Broodmother during this time.  If any of these are aggroed before the fight begins the quest will NOT work.  Broodmother will come up to the fort and attack Grakl, atwhich point and time Fergul will run like a girl towards the NE corner of the fort (NE corner is best place to set up.)  Attack and Kill Fergul Frostsky and he drops the Kromrif Military Leggings.  *NOTE  Do not try to fear Fergul.  If you do he will despawn and the quest will end without the desired item.<br>
<br>
Kromrif Military Leggings<br>
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP<br>
Slot:  LEGS<br>
AC:  14<br>
STR: +6  WIS: +5  SV DISEASE: +5  SVCOLD: +5<br>
WT: 4.0<br>
Class: ALL<br>
Race: ALL<br>
<br>
Enjoy and remember that it's not all about leveling.  It's all about the adventure.  Happy New Year TK <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub57.ezboard.com/btetsuyaknights.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flurrey>Flurrey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/1/03 12:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub57.ezboard.com/ftetsuyaknightsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=186.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Military Leggings Quest</span><hr size=1> That is an awesome quest and item!  Thanks for posting it for us all!  You mentioned that good coldain faction is needed.  What are good ways to bring up that faction?  I know that several of my chars would LOVE to obtain this!  Most are probably a wee bit tender yet.  But Tobbi certainly isn't.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub57.ezboard.com/btetsuyaknights.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cleareye1>Cleareye1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/2/03 8:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub57.ezboard.com/ftetsuyaknightsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=186.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromrif Military Leggings Quest</span><hr size=1> Best way to get Coldain faction up is to kill the giant scout thingys(can't remember there actula name) and the wolves in The Great Divide.<br>
